profile prompt in skill doesnt match the new profile structure
generic note feature: attach a freeform note to a company or a role (e.g. `jl note add --company <name>` / `jl note add --role <id>`), stored in the company/role folder. use case: documenting reusable application material like a "why <company>" essay.
skill: document that companies should be tracked BEFORE logging applications against them. it's not enforced in code (log add derives a slug from --employer either way), but tracking first links the entry to the company folder and the APPLIED rollup in `jl company ls`. consider: warn on `jl log add` when the derived/passed company isn't tracked, or auto-offer to track it.

--- features from notepad-log import (TWC work-search) ---

[P1] bulk log import: `jl log import -` that parses a pasted TWC work-search notepad block (the user keeps a stable template: Date/Activity/Job type/Employer/Address-website/Phone/Contact/Method/Result, grouped by "Week of <date>") into log entries. one-shot pipe instead of hand-adding each entry.

[P1] log add: missing employer fields required by the TX TWC form: `--phone` (employer phone) and `--address` (employer address/website, distinct from posting --url). without them a faithful report can't fill those columns.

[P1] state-vocabulary report renderer (TX TWC): map jl's controlled vocab to the exact portal labels. gaps observed: TWC distinguishes "applied online" / "sent résumé" / "applied in person" but jl collapses all to `applied` (no "sent résumé" type exists); TWC has "Workforce Solutions office"; TWC has a per-entry **Result** field ("submitted application", "awaiting response", "no reply", "interviewed", "hired", "not hired") that is distinct from jl's application `status`. render paste-ready output matching the portal field layout.

[P2] compensation/offer capture: a comp field on an offer entry or company (e.g. SpaceX: "170-210 base + 20% bonus (starbase) + 20% vest after 1yr + 10%/yr + 450k stock"). should backfill the profile salary floor/target (currently TODO in profile.md).

[P3] application threads: link follow-up activities to a parent application so one opportunity reads as a timeline, not scattered rows. observed: SpaceX Sr. IT Linux SRE (applied 3/19 -> phone interview 3/27); Base Power Backend (applied 3/23 -> online interview 4/2).

[P2] per-role change history: instead of archiving full payload copies, keep a compact change log PER ROLE. today upsert overwrites the role (roles.go ~264-274: out[i]=incoming) and discards old field values; "changed" is only a bare global_id in last-import.json (latest import only, no old->new). two event kinds, both already DETECTED in Import but not recorded: (1) CHANGED - a field's old->new (title/salary/location/url; from the roles.go:267 branch); (2) DELETED - role dropped from a fetch and marked gone (from the roles.go:285-300 gone loop), recorded with date; plus the reverse (reappeared/reposted) when a gone role returns in a later payload. store a bounded []Event on the Role (or side history.json keyed by global_id): {at, kind, field, old, new}. then `jl role show` can print a timeline (e.g. "seen 5/1, salary 200k->180k 6/15, deleted 6/20, reposted 7/2"). cheap: a few events per role << one description blob. this is the useful provenance that justifies NOT keeping raw payload archives.

[P2] store size/perf: roles.json is read+json.Unmarshal'd whole on EVERY command (store.go LoadRoles), and the `description` field dominates its bytes (~119MB for ~19k roles). gzipping roles.json is a net loss on SSD (decompress cost > IO saved per-invocation). real fix: split `description` into a side store keyed by global_id, loaded only by `jl role show`; the index `jl role ls` parses stays tiny. SEPARATELY: the import audit payloads (data/roles/imports/<date>/<Company>.json) are a REDUNDANT copy of data already normalized into roles.json. roles.json is source of truth, the import diff runs against it, and a re-fetch is cheap (verified: re-fetching Tailscale/Grafana seconds later = 0 new/0 changed/0 gone, the keyed-upsert diff is stable, no description churn on greenhouse/ashby). so default to NOT archiving payloads at all (make it opt-in via flag/config for debugging a bad scrape); the tiny last-import.json delta already covers "what changed". interim: gzip helps (manual `gzip -r data/roles/imports` = 119MB->16MB, 7.4x, jl never reads them at runtime) + a `jl prune` retention command. NOTE: the diff is order-insensitive by design (keys roles by global_id/ats:id/normalized-url into a map, compares fields, never diffs raw JSON text/array order) so "json out of order" is a non-issue.

[P2] bulk role removal: jl has no way to remove a company's roles in bulk. `jl role rm` is single-id only; `jl company rm` untracks but leaves all the company's roles in roles.json AND leaves the raw import payload under data/roles/imports/<date>/<Company>.json. removing Amazon (31616 roles) required hand-filtering roles.json in python + rm'ing the 243MB payload by hand. add e.g. `jl company rm --purge-roles <name>` (drop its roles + import payloads) and/or `jl role rm --company <slug>`. note: import payloads are kept forever per date (the imports/ dir was 362MB); consider a retention/prune command (`jl prune`) too.

[P3] interview datetime + interviewer: log entries currently store date only, but the user records interview times ("3:00-3:30 PM CDT") and interviewer (name + phone, e.g. Allison Aguirre). add optional time/datetime and interviewer contact+phone.
